 ('1', '1', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2015-04-26 20:07:23', '2015-04-26 20:07:23', '380c0995-0e0f-4b6c-a355-137228a7b33b'),
 ('2', '2', 'en_us', 'Home', '<p>Its true, this site doesnt have a whole lot of content yet, but dont worry. Our web developers have just installed the CMS, and theyre setting things up for the content editors this very moment. Soon Graceux.dev will be an oasis of fresh perspectives, sharp analyses, and astute opinions that will keep you coming back again and again.</p>', NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2015-04-26 20:07:25', '2015-08-25 03:42:06', '51da843e-df63-4022-adf3-f01624610c89'),
 ('4', '4', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2015-04-26 20:37:35', '2015-04-26 20:37:35', '9d3fea36-5d9c-4412-bae9-e6c789387588'),
 ('5', '5', 'en_us', 'About', NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2015-04-29 01:58:37', '2015-04-29 01:58:37', '8f6b3c95-fa16-411b-9b38-0fe96778838d'),
 ('6', '6', 'en_us', 'Real-Time Fengshui', NULL, 'The project is designed to present abstract feng shui principles, its philosophy, as well as its applications in modern interior design through creative 3D interactive experience.', '2014', '[\"aftereffects\",\"flash\",\"photoshop\",\"blender\",\"html5\",\"sketch\",\"webgl\"]', '', '', 'UX, Interface Design, Modeling & Visual Design, User Research &Testing, Content Strategy', 'Real-Time\r\nFengshui', NULL, '', '', 'Project Brief', '<p>The Real-time Experience is an interactive educational project that\r\nintroduces daily feng shui tips to college students, office workers, and anyone who wants to learn\r\nhow feng shui can enhance their lives. This project uses Web GL technology that runs on any\r\ncomputer with an up-to-date, modern browser.\r\n</p><p>The user flow is a simple four-step process: listen, observe, find, and solve. This is how\r\nfeng shui masters help people figure out their problems. It is an engaging practice because\r\nusers become actively involved in the whole problem-solving experience. My goal for this\r\nproject is to present the principles and rules of feng shui philosophy, as well as its applications\r\nin modern interior design and to interpret feng shui through creative interactive experience. I\r\nwish that by introducing feng shui to new western audience, they can benefit from learning\r\nfeng shui theories and improve their living environment. </p>', 'What I\'ve Learned', '<p>During my user testing process, I found that most people skip over intro tours as quickly as possible ant those that didn\'t rarely remember what they were supposed to learn, because they haven\'t seen the interface yet so they don\'t have any sense of where and how the tips they\'re learning will apply. Here comes the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Just_in_Time_Teaching\" target=\"_blank\">Just In Time Education</a><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Just_in_Time_Teaching\" target=\"_blank\"></a><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Just_in_Time_Teaching\"></a> concept.<br></p><p>I\'ve tried different methods to solve this problem. For example, by overlaying the tuts on top of the actual interface design, but even so, people lack the experience to know ehich actions will be useful to them and when. Besides, over time they\'ve likely to forget some of the functions since they didn\'t take that action immediately after they\'ve learnt. </p><p>So instead of trying to teach everything up front and all at once, teach in the moment when specific information is actually useful. In my case, I tried to provide only the nessasary tips for visitors, for instance, if a user start exploring the 3D scence by click, I will suggest him scroll mouse wheel, vice versa. Besides, . Last but not least, the \"how to\" instruction is always on the left corner of the page, make it easier for visitors to check out anytime.</p><p>The trick to getting just in time education right is revealing useful information when people actually need it not when they don\'t.</p>', 'Subject Research & Analysis', '<p>Feng shui, as a theory that is a bit obscure, makes most of its regarding websites less interesting in design. During the existing products research I\'ve conducted, the common problems is: the related cultural symbols and patterns tend to be abused, and with a page full of incomprehensible theories, it appears to be pseudoscience. Ultimately, they all contribute to an obscure reading experience that one can feel difficult to learn from. Actually, the common design pattern is using some relevant images (or even irrelevant ones) surrounding textural information. The common design issues are: Heavy copy, irrelevant links; Long pages of overwhelming information; Most Feng shui introduce this theory in an imperative tone.</p><p>In contrary, I\'d like to introduce this theory through storytelling and teach its principals through real-time problem solving, as well as give the user down-to-earth tips.</p><p>I also curious about what is the best learning curve/format for users? What is the ideally opening story for those site visitors without background information about fengshui at all? What makes users excited about the fengshui and what benefit them the most? I come up a questionaire with 9 questions and asked 19 target audience* to fill the survey. To my surprise, most respondents would like to jump into practical and visualized case study which can be applied to daily life. Here are a summary of the research:</p><ul><li>88.9% of respondents are looking for basic and simple feng shui advices.</li><li>Their main interests in feng shui relate to how this concept can be used in real life.</li><li>Users are expecting a visualized interactive learning process.</li></ul><p>* The target audience are the generation aged between 18 - 35, such as college students, or young couples who have an interest in building their living environment. Also including those who has an interest in online learning.</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Interactive Experience', 'http://realtimefengshui.com/', 'blue', '0', '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2015-04-29 04:17:46', '2015-10-17 22:01:20', 'd89d67f2-affa-448e-a570-c4c742205bb9'),
