 ('10', '10', 'en_us', 'LivePerson Pricing Model Design', NULL, 'I led the UX design for LivePerson where I worked. My goal is to reshape the brands online presence by creating a sleek user interface and transferring the focus to B2C.', '2014', '[\"photoshop\"]', 'LivePerson', 'http://www.liveperson.com/', 'Visual Design', 'LivePerson\r\nPricing Model\r\nDesign', NULL, '', '', 'Project Brief', '<p>I led the website UX design for LivePerson global where I worked. The goal I set is to reshape the brands online presence, through creating a sleek user interface and transferring the site focus to B2C which would offer more engaging online experiences for customers.</p><p>As a IA and UX person, I conducted researches and came up with a series of ideations before planning and restructuring the site, followed by some important considerations from both design and development point of view.</p>', 'What I\'ve Learned', '<p>I\'ve learned a lot.</p>', 'Analysis Heading', '<p>This is the analysis text.\r\n</p><ul>\r\n	<li>The page doesn\'t impress me, as a first-time visitor after seeing a few slides in the header image area. It simply was not able to convey what it is.</li>\r\n	<li>The look and feel of the overall layout didn\'t match its content. The logo could also be redesigned to be more coherent to a writer\'s community.</li>\r\n	<li>There is no quick upload functionality for sharing your work and the sign up process is too long.</li>\r\n	<li>Kanjy allows writers to create portfolios of their work, but it\'s still not sufficient to make the whole community an active network.</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, 'Web Design', '', 'yellow', '0', '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2015-04-30 03:30:18', '2015-08-29 21:43:01', '45c76090-8594-4c2b-b08b-93adee7aed2e'),
 ('12', '12', 'en_us', 'Composer Hsin-Lei Chen Portfolio', NULL, 'An online listening experience and artist\'s archive for Hsin-Lei Chen, a Taiwanese composer who is known for her experimental folk music.', '2015', '[\"photoshop\",\"css3\",\"html5\",\"javascript\",\"sketch\",\"webgl\"]', 'Hsin-Lei Chen', 'http://hsinlei.com', 'Visual Design, User Experience Design', 'Composer\r\nHsin-Lei Chen\r\nPortfolio', NULL, 'Composer Hsin-Lei Chen Portfolio', 'This is the OG description.', 'Project Brief', '<p>I\'ve got a chance to make a portfolio website for Hsin-Lei: a friend of mine, and a talented classical/experimental music composer.</p><p>To fully understand Hsin-Lei\'s music before determining the art direction, we kept discussing about her musical pieces and exchanging my design blueprints with her feedbacks. I found her styles were heavily influenced by the European masters of classical music. Grown up and rooted in Chinese culture, most of her songs are also relevant to traditional Chinese literature and philosophies, flavored her work with some unique Asian tastes. Those conversations inspired me of a multimedia website, which represents the essential spirits of her work, using a calm color palette and some stylish photography.\r\n</p>', 'What I\'ve Learned', '<p>A good design for a musical portfolio is not just playing some lovely tunes. It expresses the deepest feelings and emotions of the composer. Following with this direction, a multi-media form of experience can resonate with the audience. Besides, social share is one of the big consideration for this project.</p><p>Another interesting thing Ive observed during the test is all the 3 male testers click on the album first, while female users tend to click through the menu tabs, or the main navigation. Male testers performed better at using different controlling mechanisms to navigate through the site, like mouse-scroll or click-and-drag, whereas female testers usually rely on mouse-click.</p>', 'Project Analysis', '<p>I want Hsin-Lei\'s portfolio to archive her music background and career history, as a press kit. The steps to create a portfolio involve documenting her career path, arranging her work based on that and choosing a proper presentation form. Here are some ideas to expose her talents through making this portfolio a unique spot on the Internet, and shareable.</p><p><br>\r\n</p><ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Photography</strong>\r\n	Her portfolio should display a artistic portrait representing the image she wants to convey. Since Hsin-Lei works as an independent composer, I proposed a close shot to fill the frame as much as possible. An extra finding during our conversation is that Hsin-Lei is a visual person: through her studies and travelings, she records inspirations by shooting photos. Many of her music pieces were finished with the reference of those image resources and abstract sketches.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Biography</strong> Since Hsin-Lei only had a press blog before, for content strategy and SEO purpose, a biography statement documenting her styles and accomplishments will help visitors uncover some prospects of her music.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Playlist </strong>Make a list of her selected work, whose length will change by the number of songs. It needs a responsive design so that the site will appear just as good even when the list becomes very long. The order of songs should be adjustable so Hsin-Lei can always choose to display her proudest work on the top.\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<strong>Awards</strong>\r\n	\r\n	Cleverly use page spaces to display her awards by using feature articles. If she had released an album, include good reviews and reviewers\' quotes for it.</li><li><strong>Content Management</strong> The building of the portfolio is a continuous commitment and evolve along with her career. So its contents should be manageable via a CMS.</li></ul>', NULL, NULL, 'Web Application', 'http://hsinlei.com', 'blue', '0', '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2015-05-06 02:06:58', '2015-11-11 05:00:50', '75ff3a9c-f4da-4a67-8051-e0efe173d286'),
