 ('18', '22', 'en_us', 'Cazenovia Beverage Trail', NULL, 'The Cazenovia Beverage Trail, is a agrotourism endeavor. It is seeking quotes to develop and design a website that encompasses and portrays the vision and goals of the organization.', '2013', '[\"photoshop\",\"css3\",\"html5\",\"javascript\"]', 'Cazenovia Beverage Trail', '', 'UX Design, Visual Design, Development', 'Cazenovia\r\nBeverage Trail', NULL, '', '', 'Project Brief', '<p>The Cazenovia Beverage Trail, aka CBT, is a agrotourism endeavor. It is seeking quotes to develop and design a website that encompasses and portrays the vision and goals of the organization.\r\n</p><p>I designed the website with a primary focus on the promotional area. As CBT aims on driving customers and potential partners to its committee to further its tourism growth. I took photographs on the site of attractions, created a 3D navigation menu that is fun to play with, and a dedicated section giving quick informations of its daily activities.\r\n</p>', 'What I\'ve Learned', '<p>This is what I\'ve learned.</p>', 'Project Analysis', '<p>Sed ut perspiciatis unde omnis iste natus error sit voluptatem accusantium doloremque laudantium, totam rem aperiam, eaque ipsa quae ab illo inventore veritatis et quasi architecto beatae vitae dicta sunt explicabo.</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Website', '', 'red', '0', '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2015-05-06 02:40:58', '2015-09-09 03:39:07', '02cb27d2-b00a-4bb5-b59b-d9c851d62fe4'),
 ('19', '24', 'en_us', 'Party Planner', NULL, 'Party Planner is a web application that helps restaurants and bars book available spaces online.', '2014', '[\"justinmind\"]', '', '', 'UX Design, Wireframe', 'Party Planner', NULL, '', '', 'Project Brief', '<p>Party Planner is a web application that helps restaurants and bars book available spaces online. I was responsible for creating the hi-fi wireframes, including responsive layout, user dashboard, and the mobile application interface design.</p>', 'What I\'ve Learned', '<p>This is what I\'ve learned.</p>', 'Project Analysis', '<p>This is the project analysis texts.</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Web Application Design', '', 'red', '0', '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2015-05-06 02:43:23', '2015-08-31 05:02:47', '6f0bca6f-b031-46dc-a323-dd1fb67bf2d2'),
 ('20', '26', 'en_us', 'Kanjy Website', NULL, 'A community platform dedicated to emerging and established screenwriters, playwrights, agents, producers, organizations and venues.', '2013', '[\"Adobe InDesign\",\"photoshop\",\"justinmind\"]', 'Kanjy', 'https://kanjy.co/', 'UX Design, Wireframe, Prototype', 'Kanjy\r\nWebsite', NULL, '', '', 'Project Brief', '<p>Kanjy is a community platform dedicated to emerging and established screenwriters, playwrights, agents, producers, organizations and venues. The original website could be found at <a href=\"https://kanjy.co/\">https://kanjy.co/</a>\r\n</p><p>Kanjy\'s objective is to provide a single platform that can connect and organize vast artist communities specifically related to writers. However there are several problems on the site that might drag Kanjy away from even more traffic:\r\n</p><ul>\r\n	<li>The page doesn\'t impress me, as a first-time visitor after seeing a few slides in the header image area. It simply was not able to convey what it is.</li>\r\n	<li>The look and feel of the overall layout didn\'t match its content. The logo could also be redesigned to be more coherent to a writer\'s community.</li>\r\n	<li>There is no quick upload functionality for sharing your work and the sign up process is too long.</li>\r\n	<li>Kanjy allows writers to create portfolios of their work, but it\'s still not sufficient to make the whole community an active network.</li>\r\n	<li>The connection between writers and publishers needs to be tightened as an even closer relationship. I tried to solve these issues by adapting a near black and white color scheme, which is inspired by newspaper and hand writing imageries. Adding a quick upload button for registered users to submit their work as soon as they want. Encouraging a new user to join by showing the numbers of the current user base (writer, agents, producers, organizations and venues) and created a Author of the Week section in the home page. Finally, the site was made responsive for users to read and share from almost any given platform.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'What I\'ve Learned', '<p>This is what I\'ve learned.</p>', 'UX Research & Analytics', '<p>This Kanjy heat map may not pretty at all, but it conveys important information: </p><ul><li>Although the signup button is so bold and highly contrast, it does not lead to a click.</li><li>Users would like to to click the pagination dot. This suggest they want to learn more about KANJI, however, on the other side, the first slider didn\'t provide enough information.</li><li>The \"script\" search button on the top is also a heat spot, it may suggest users would like to have a overall tour and know more about Kanjy before they decide to join the community.</li><li>The scroll map shows if users would like to scroll down to the end, luckily, since Kanjy\'s page isn\'t that long, and most users scroll down to the footer. However, visitor stop scrolling immediately when they meet the footer, it may indicate that the footer\'s information usually be considered as lower hierarchy.</li><li>Irregular color bar in the scroll map suggests users did read instead of just moving, it also tells that visitors would like to explore more. </li></ul>', NULL, NULL, 'Responsive Web Design', 'https://kanjy.co/', 'green', '0', '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2015-05-06 02:50:43', '2015-08-31 04:29:26', '9af16ad9-768a-44ef-b4ef-3eedb3ccc05d'),
