 ('145', '184', 'en_us', 'ACCPI Community Website', NULL, ' I have taken this project from half-way, and the idea, use flow and even marketing strategy has been changed a lot from our original plan.', '2015', '[\"photoshop\",\"axure\",\"sketch\"]', 'LivePerson', 'http://www.liveperson.com/', 'Researches, Wireframes, UX Design & Testing', 'ACCPI\r\nCommunity Website', NULL, 'ACCPI Community Website', ' I have taken this project from half-way, and the idea, use flow and even marketing strategy has been changed a lot from our original plan.', 'Project Brief', '<p>My design goal is to gather a thriving global profession of best-in-class customer cares experts across all industries, and LP also influences the community by sharing knowledge and provides trainings as industry lead; Builds up a member-driven organization committed to promoting customer care and customer engagement as a competitive advantage in business; This website can be a soft sale tool that Introduce LP\'s 2.0 platform, mobile applications and its benefits.</p><p>I led the website UX design for ACCPI commnity site. The goal is to reshape the LivePerson\'s (LP) brands online presence, through creating a sleek sharable community experiences and transferring the site focus to nurturing a customer care professional which would offer more engaging online experiences for customers. As a IA and UX person, I conducted researches and came up with a series of ideations before planning and restructuring the site, followed by important considerations from both design and development point of view. Here is a work in progress for ACCPI website.\r\n</p><ul>\r\n	<li>Research & analysis</li>\r\n	<li>IA & sitemap</li>\r\n	<li>Persona</li>\r\n	<li>Use flow</li>\r\n	<li>Wireframes</li>\r\n	<li>Interactive prototype</li>\r\n	<li>Testing</li>\r\n</ul>', 'What I\'ve Learned', '<p>I have taken this project from half-way, and the idea, use flow and even marketing strategy has been changed a lot from our original plan. To coincide with the a series of the campaign, our team was under extreme pressure to move fast. We were tasked to deliver from ideation to highfidelity prototype to our technical production partner within 4 weeks, so it requires quick turnarounds. The combination of a fixed deadline, content strategy, usability testing, and usability testing meant I needed to get the experience right in the first two weeks.</p>', 'Reaserch & Analysis', '<p>When were thinking about acquiring users, its easy to assume that \"friction\" is the enemy of traction. Thats why many products make signing up so simple  the fewer fields, the better. But that only really works when your users satisfaction doesnt depend on other users. In the case of a web platform, such as a social network or marketplace, the quality of users and their interactions define a good product and experience. In fact, to achieve scale in a platform model, good UX design often requires that you filter out bad users.\r\n</p><p>Think about Product Hunt. If anyone could post a product, spammers would turn the experience into a 24/7 infomercial. By requiring a nomination from the most engaged and thoughtful contributors in the community, theyre carefully curating the content by first curating the people who can post.\r\n</p><p>Even in products that dont focus on community-generated content, user quality still matters. Think about a dating website like Match.com or caregiving site Care.com. For these sites, the users <em>are</em> the product. So some level of friction in the sign-up process will help deter or actively block bad eggs. But it is also true that visitors cannot fill everything out at the first stage, so it is also important to create a progress profile completion system like Linkedin.\r\n</p><p>So what motivated customer care professionals to join our community? Besides the attractive game campaigns, the material reward, maybe we should think inside out, about how our community can encourage them to learn, share and resonate with other people with same interests and experiences.\r\n</p><p>The key concept to understand is that <strong>motivation</strong> is difficult to change. Don\'t focus on it. Rewards are great but not effective <strong>unless they perform the behavior first.</strong>\r\n</p>', NULL, NULL, 'Web Design', 'https://accpi.org/', 'yellow', '0', '0', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', '2015-08-25 03:41:28', '2015-11-11 05:19:33', '86807b21-b8b1-433e-971c-6c30a227db5c'),
