 ('365', '26', '3', '1', 'en_us', '18', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Kanjy Website\",\"slug\":\"kanjy-website\",\"postDate\":1430880600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"24\":\"<p>This Kanjy heat map may not pretty at all, but it conveys important information: <\\/p><ul><li>Although the signup button is so bold and highly contrast, it does not lead to a click.<\\/li><li><span><\\/span>Users would like to to click the pagination dot. This suggest they want to learn more about KANJI, however, on the other side, the first slider didn\'t provide enough information.<\\/li><li>The \\\"script\\\" search button on the top is also a heat spot, it may suggest users would like to have a overall tour and know more about Kanjy before they decide to join the community.<\\/li><li>The scroll map shows if users would like to scroll down to the end, luckily, since Kanjy\'s page isn\'t that long, and most users scroll down to the footer. However, visitor stop scrolling immediately when they meet the footer, it may indicate that the footer\'s information usually be considered as lower hierarchy.<\\/li><li>Irregular color bar in the scroll map suggests users did read instead of just moving, it also tells that visitors would like to explore more. <\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"39\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"step\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"311\"]}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"step\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"312\"]}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"step\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"313\"]}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"step\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"314\"]}},\"new5\":{\"type\":\"step\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"315\"]}},\"new6\":{\"type\":\"step\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"316\"]}}},\"23\":\"UX Research & Analytics\",\"20\":\"<p>Kanjy is a community platform dedicated to emerging and established screenwriters, playwrights, agents, producers, organizations and venues. The original website could be found at <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/kanjy.co\\/\\\">https:\\/\\/kanjy.co\\/<\\/a>\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Kanjy\'s objective is to provide a single platform that can connect and organize vast artist communities specifically related to writers. However there are several problems on the site that might drag Kanjy away from even more traffic:\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>The page doesn\'t impress me, as a first-time visitor after seeing a few slides in the header image area. It simply was not able to convey what it is.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>The look and feel of the overall layout didn\'t match its content. The logo could also be redesigned to be more coherent to a writer\'s community.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>There is no quick upload functionality for sharing your work and the sign up process is too long.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Kanjy allows writers to create portfolios of their work, but it\'s still not sufficient to make the whole community an active network.<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>The connection between writers and publishers needs to be tightened as an even closer relationship. I tried to solve these issues by adapting a near black and white color scheme, which is inspired by newspaper and hand writing imageries. Adding a quick upload button for registered users to submit their work as soon as they want. Encouraging a new user to join by showing the numbers of the current user base (writer, agents, producers, organizations and venues) and created a \\u201cAuthor of the Week\\u201d section in the home page. Finally, the site was made responsive for users to read and share from almost any given platform.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\",\"19\":\"Project Brief\",\"10\":\"Kanjy\",\"11\":\"https:\\/\\/kanjy.co\\/\",\"58\":\"green\",\"25\":{\"27\":{\"type\":\"mediaFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Feature 1\",\"body\":\"<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua. Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris nisi ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis aute irure dolor in reprehenderit in voluptate velit esse cillum dolore eu fugiat nulla pariatur.<\\/p>\",\"media\":[\"152\",\"151\"],\"layout\":\"fluid\",\"device\":\"none\",\"allowEnlarge\":\"1\"}},\"154\":{\"type\":\"mediaFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Very nice details\",\"body\":\"<p>This is a description for the very nice details image.<\\/p>\",\"media\":[\"153\"],\"layout\":\"full\",\"device\":\"none\",\"allowEnlarge\":\"\"}}},\"49\":\"Responsive Web Design\",\"14\":\"Kanjy\\r\\nWebsite\",\"22\":\"<p>This is what I\'ve learned.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"What I\'ve Learned\",\"43\":[\"93\"],\"17\":\"\",\"18\":\"\",\"16\":\"\",\"13\":[\"7\"],\"42\":[\"118\"],\"50\":\"https:\\/\\/kanjy.co\\/\",\"44\":[\"76\"],\"12\":\"UX Design, Wireframe, Prototype\",\"3\":\"A community platform dedicated to emerging and established screenwriters, playwrights, agents, producers, organizations and venues.\",\"9\":[\"Adobe InDesign\",\"photoshop\",\"justinmind\"],\"4\":\"2013\"}}', '2015-08-31 04:19:11', '2015-08-31 04:19:11', '12150ee2-174a-4bfe-b677-68c1f85caf0f'),
