 ('369', '184', '3', '1', 'en_us', '17', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"ACCPI Community Website\",\"slug\":\"accpi\",\"postDate\":1440474060,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"24\":\"<p>When we\\u2019re thinking about acquiring users, it\\u2019s easy to assume that \\\"friction\\\" is the enemy of traction. That\\u2019s why many products make signing up so simple \\u2014 the fewer fields, the better. But that only really works when your user\\u2019s satisfaction doesn\\u2019t depend on other users. In the case of a web platform, such as a social network or marketplace, the quality of users and their interactions define a good product and experience. In fact, to achieve scale in a platform model, good UX design often requires that you filter out bad users.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Think about Product Hunt. If anyone could post a product, spammers would turn the experience into a 24\\/7 infomercial. By requiring a nomination from \\u201cthe most engaged and thoughtful contributors\\u201d in the community, they\\u2019re carefully curating the content by first curating the people who can post.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Even in products that don\\u2019t focus on community-generated content, user quality still matters. Think about a dating website like Match.com or caregiving site Care.com. For these sites, the users <em>are<\\/em> the product. So some level of friction in the sign-up process will help deter or actively block bad eggs. But it is also true that visitors cannot fill everything out at the first stage, so it is also important to create a progress profile completion system like Linkedin.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>So what motivated customer care professionals to join our community? Besides the attractive game campaigns, the material reward, maybe we should think inside out, about how our community can encourage them to learn, share and resonate with other people with same interests and experiences.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>The key concept to understand is that <strong>motivation<\\/strong> is difficult to change. Don\'t focus on it. Rewards are great but not effective <strong>unless they perform the behavior first.<\\/strong>\\r\\n<\\/p>\",\"39\":\"\",\"23\":\"Reaserch & Analysis\",\"20\":\"<p>My design goal is to gather a thriving global profession of best-in-class customer cares experts across all industries, and LP also influences the community by sharing knowledge and provides trainings as industry lead; Builds up a member-driven organization committed to promoting customer care and customer engagement as a competitive advantage in business; This website can be a soft sale tool that Introduce LP\'s 2.0 platform, mobile applications and its benefits.<\\/p><p>I led the website UX design for ACCPI commnity site. The goal is to reshape the LivePerson\'s (LP) brand\\u2019s online presence, through creating a sleek sharable community experiences and transferring the site focus to nurturing a customer care professional which would offer more engaging online experiences for customers. As a IA and UX person, I conducted researches and came up with a series of ideations before planning and restructuring the site, followed by important considerations from both design and development point of view. Here is a work in progress for ACCPI website.\\r\\n<\\/p><ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Research & analysis<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>IA & sitemap<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Persona<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Use flow<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Wireframes<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Interactive prototype<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Testing<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\",\"19\":\"Project Brief\",\"10\":\"LivePerson\",\"11\":\"http:\\/\\/www.liveperson.com\\/\",\"58\":\"yellow\",\"25\":{\"185\":{\"type\":\"mediaFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Persona\",\"body\":\"<p>In order to demostrate our target audience for ACCPI, I\'ve created 5 personas, here list two as examples. Their working experience level as a customer care professional is about junior to mid-weight. Full persona list and analysis will be provided by request.<\\/p>\",\"media\":[\"182\",\"183\"],\"layout\":\"full\",\"device\":\"none\",\"allowEnlarge\":\"\"}},\"189\":{\"type\":\"mediaFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"User Flow\",\"body\":\"<p>Back to my analysis before, I think the community will be relatively open unless visitor wants to take action. The trigger can be the game, the social press of our community but most important, the ACCPI website content itself.<\\/p>\",\"media\":[\"188\"],\"layout\":\"full\",\"device\":\"none\",\"allowEnlarge\":\"1\"}},\"187\":{\"type\":\"mediaFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Sitemap\",\"body\":\"<p>Back to my analysis before, I think the community will be relatively open unless visitor wants to take action. The trigger can be the game, the social press of our community but most important, the ACCPI website content itself.<\\/p>\",\"media\":[\"186\"],\"layout\":\"full\",\"device\":\"none\",\"allowEnlarge\":\"1\"}},\"191\":{\"type\":\"mediaFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Wireframes\",\"body\":\"<p>Sed ut perspiciatis unde omnis iste natus error sit voluptatem accusantium doloremque laudantium, totam rem aperiam, eaque ipsa quae ab illo inventore veritatis et quasi architecto beatae vitae dicta sunt explicabo. Nemo enim ipsam voluptatem quia voluptas sit aspernatur aut odit aut fugit, sed quia consequuntur magni dolores eos qui ratione voluptatem sequi nesciunt.<\\/p>\",\"media\":[\"192\",\"193\",\"194\"],\"layout\":\"fluid\",\"device\":\"none\",\"allowEnlarge\":\"1\"}},\"196\":{\"type\":\"mediaFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Finished Design\",\"body\":\"\",\"media\":[\"195\"],\"layout\":\"full\",\"device\":\"none\",\"allowEnlarge\":\"\"}},\"217\":{\"type\":\"comparisonFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Site Control & Test\",\"body\":\"<p>Sed ut perspiciatis unde omnis iste natus error sit voluptatem accusantium doloremque laudantium, totam rem aperiam, eaqu