 ('470', '6', '3', '1', 'en_us', '94', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Real-Time Fengshui\",\"slug\":\"real-time-fengshui\",\"postDate\":1430281020,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"24\":\"<p>During the existing products research I\'ve conducted, the common problems is: the related cultural symbols and patterns tend to be abused, and with a page full of incomprehensible theories, it appears to be pseudoscience. Ultimately, they all contribute to an obscure reading experience that one can feel difficult to learn from. <\\/p><p>In Contrary, with my project, Real-time Fengshui, I\'d like to introduce this theory through storytelling and teach its principals through real-time problem solving, as well as give the user down-to-earth tips.<\\/p><p>I also curious about what is the best learning curve\\/format for users? What is the ideally opening story for those site visitors without background information about fengshui at all? What makes users excited about the fengshui and what benefit them the most? I come up a questionaire with 9 questions and asked 19 target audience* to fill the survey. To my surprise, most respondents would like to jump into practical and visualized case study which can be applied to daily life. <\\/p><p>* College students and young office workers who have an interest in different cultures and open to new ideas. <\\/p>\",\"39\":{\"56\":{\"type\":\"step\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"99\"]}},\"55\":{\"type\":\"step\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"98\"]}}},\"23\":\"Subject Research & Analysis\",\"20\":\"<p>The Real-time Experience is an interactive 3D design project that\\r\\nintroduces daily feng shui tips to college students, office workers, and anyone who wants to learn\\r\\nhow feng shui can enhance their lives. This project uses Web GL technology that runs on any\\r\\ncomputer with an up-to-date, modern browser.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>The user flow is a simple four-step process: \\u201clisten