 when users enter rooms,\\r\\na thank you page when users finished all the tasks in the rooms, and during the exploring\\r\\nprocess, the characters are on the bottom righthand corner of the screen and will occasionally\\r\\n\\u201cping\\u201d the visitors some hints. Users can click the characters and ask for those clues as well.<\\/p>\",\"media\":[\"178\"],\"layout\":\"full\",\"device\":\"none\",\"allowEnlarge\":\"\"}},\"68\":{\"type\":\"mediaFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Feature 3\",\"body\":\"<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Vestibulum auctor in urna ac malesuada. Pellentesque eu erat nulla. Vivamus blandit tempus nisi efficitur placerat. Sed sit amet purus vehicula, venenatis turpis ut, commodo orci. Nunc pellentesque velit eu sem vulputate dignissim non sed eros. Donec convallis nisi id ex elementum, a rhoncus mauris tincidunt. Donec egestas risus et ex efficitur sodales.<\\/p>\",\"media\":[\"157\",\"86\",\"84\",\"85\"],\"layout\":\"fluid\",\"device\":\"none\",\"allowEnlarge\":\"\"}},\"60\":{\"type\":\"comparisonFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Simple Interactions\",\"body\":\"<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Vestibulum auctor in urna ac malesuada. Pellentesque eu erat nulla. Vivamus blandit tempus nisi efficitur placerat. Sed sit amet purus vehicula, venenatis turpis ut, commodo orci. Nunc pellentesque velit eu sem vulputate dignissim non sed eros. Donec convallis nisi id ex elementum, a rhoncus mauris tincidunt. Donec egestas risus et ex efficitur sodales.<\\/p>\",\"images\":[\"97\",\"96\"],\"firstCaption\":\"Before Interaction\",\"secondCaption\":\"After Interaction\",\"fadeEnabled\":\"\"}}},\"49\":\"Interactive Experience\",\"14\":\"Real-Time\\r\\nFengshui\",\"22\":\"<p>Just In Time Education<br><\\/p><p>During my user testing process, I found that most people skip over intro tours as quickly as possible ant those that didn\'t rarely remember what they were supposed to learn, because they haven\'t seen the interface yet so they don\'t have any sense of where and how the tips they\'re learning will apply.<\\/p><p>I\'ve tried different methods to solve this problem. For example, by overlaying the tuts on top of the actual interface design, but even so, people lack the experience to know ehich actions will be useful to them and when. Besides, over time they\'ve likely to forget some of the functions since they didn\'t take that action immediately after they\'ve learnt. <\\/p><p>So instead of trying to teach everything up front and all at once, teach in the moment when specific information is actually useful. In my case, I tried to provide only the nessasary tips for visitors, for instance, if a user start exploring the 3D scence by click, I will suggest him scroll mouse wheel, vice versa. Besides, <\\/p><p>The trick to getting just in time education right is revealing useful information when people actually need it not when they don\'t.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"What I\'ve Learned\",\"43\":[\"92\"],\"17\":\"\",\"18\":\"\",\"16\":\"\",\"13\":[\"7\"],\"42\":[\"110\"],\"50\":\"http:\\/\\/realtimefengshui.com\\/\",\"44\":[\"80\"],\"12\":\"UX, Interface Design, Modeling & Visual Design, User Research &Testing, Content Strategy\",\"3\":\"The project is designed to present abstract feng shui principles, its philosophy, as well as its applications in modern interior design through creative 3D interactive experience.\",\"9\":[\"aftereffects\",\"flash\",\"photoshop\",\"blender\",\"html5\",\"sketch\",\"webgl\"],\"4\":\"2014\"}}', '2015-10-13 03:04:08', '2015-10-13 03:04:08', 'd0300fe0-cd2d-4a8e-861e-22d483fafeea'),
