such as college students, or young couples who have an interest in building their living environment. Also including those who has an interest in online learning.<\\/p>\",\"39\":{\"56\":{\"type\":\"step\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"99\"]}},\"55\":{\"type\":\"step\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"98\"]}}},\"23\":\"Subject Research & Analysis\",\"20\":\"<p>The Real-time Experience is an interactive educational project that\\r\\nintroduces daily feng shui tips to college students, office workers, and anyone who wants to learn\\r\\nhow feng shui can enhance their lives. This project uses Web GL technology that runs on any\\r\\ncomputer with an up-to-date, modern browser.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>The user flow is a simple four-step process: \\u201clisten,\\u201d \\u201cobserve,\\u201d \\u201cfind,\\u201d and \\u201csolve.\\u201d This is how\\r\\nfeng shui masters help people figure out their problems. It is an engaging practice because\\r\\nusers become actively involved in the whole problem-solving experience. My goal for this\\r\\nproject is to present the principles and rules of feng shui philosophy, as well as its applications\\r\\nin modern interior design and to interpret feng shui through creative interactive experience. I\\r\\nwish that by introducing feng shui to new western audience, they can benefit from learning\\r\\nfeng shui theories and improve their living environment. <\\/p>\",\"19\":\"Project Brief\",\"10\":\"\",\"11\":\"\",\"58\":\"blue\",\"25\":{\"21\":{\"type\":\"mediaFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Ideation \",\"body\":\"<p>Then I have an idea, instead of thinking how to covert new visitors to this topic, I\'d like to explore how feng shui theory can actually retain audience and what makes those audience addicted, so my next step is to discover the secrets of feng shui master. After watching videos, look up books and even attend several seminars by myself, I realized the people who really find feng shu helps their lives are those who has experienced confusion and then by asking someone who have a knowledge of feng shui (a feng shui master). And a feng shui master really do research and provide adaptive suggestions based on situations. <\\/p><p>Also there are a lot of active verb in feng shui, like change, add, replace. Which is very direct and easy to follow, just like Call To Action in web and poster design.<\\/p>\",\"media\":[\"469\",\"470\",\"468\"],\"layout\":\"full\",\"device\":\"none\",\"allowEnlarge\":\"1\"}},\"162\":{\"type\":\"mediaFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Wireframe & Interaction\",\"body\":\"<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Vestibulum auctor in urna ac malesuada. Pellentesque eu erat nulla. Vivamus blandit tempus nisi efficitur placerat. Sed sit amet purus vehicula, venenatis turpis ut, commodo orci. Nunc pellentesque velit eu sem vulputate dignissim non sed eros. Donec convallis nisi id ex elementum, a rhoncus mauris tincidunt. Donec egestas risus et ex efficitur sodales.<\\/p>\",\"media\":[\"161\",\"160\",\"159\"],\"layout\":\"full\",\"device\":\"desktop\",\"allowEnlarge\":\"\"}},\"61\":{\"type\":\"mediaFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Character Design\",\"body\":\"<p>The appearances of game characters, or the Fengshui clients are designed based on their different backgrounds.<\\/p><p>For example, Ollie is a character of distinguishable look because her job is in the fashion industry. The home owner Scott is a university professor in the Department of Mathematics. He is designed to look thoughtful and dressed conservatively.<\\/p>\",\"media\":[\"158\",\"175\",\"174\"],\"layout\":\"fluid\",\"device\":\"none\",\"allowEnlarge\":\"\"}},\"179\":{\"type\":\"mediaFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Conversation Design\",\"body\":\"<p>To make the Fengshui 3D experience more engaging, introducing characters into this project\\r\\nwas an innovative approach. The characters have a welcome page when users enter rooms,\\r\\na thank you page when users finished all the tasks in the rooms, and during the exploring\\r\\nprocess, the characters are on the bottom righthand corner of the screen and will occasionally\\r\\n\\u201cping\\u201d the visitors some hints. Users can click the characters and ask for those clues as well.<\\/p>\",\"media\":[\"178\"],\"layout\":\"full\",\"device\":\"none\",\"allowEnlarge\":\"\"}},\"68\":{\"type\":\"mediaFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Feature 3\",\"body\":\"<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Vestibulum auctor in urna ac malesuada. Pellentesque eu erat nulla. Vivamus blandit tempus nisi efficitur placerat. Sed sit amet purus vehicula, venenatis turpis ut, commodo orci. Nunc pellentesque velit eu sem vulputate dignissim non sed eros. Donec convallis nisi id ex elementum, a rhoncus mauris tincidunt. Donec egestas risus et ex efficitur sodales.<\\/p>\",\"media\":[\"86\",\"84\",\"85\"],\"layout\":\"fluid\",\"device\":\"none\",\"allowEnlarge\":\"\"}},\"60\":{\"type\":\"comparisonFeature\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Simple Interactions\",\"body\":\"<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Vestibulum auctor in urna ac malesuada. Pellentesque eu erat nulla. Vivamus blandit tempus nisi efficitur placerat. Sed sit amet purus vehicula, venenatis turpis ut, commodo orci. Nunc pellentesque velit eu sem vulputate dignissim non sed eros. Donec convallis nisi id ex elementum, a rhoncus mauris tincidunt. Donec egestas risus et ex efficitur sodales.<\\/p>\",\"images\":[\"97\",\"96\"],\"firstCaption\":\"Before Interaction\",\"secondCaption\":\"After Interaction\",\"fadeEnabled\":\"\"}}},\"49\":\"Interactive Experience\",\"14\":\"Real-Time\\r\\nFengshui\",\"22\":\"<p>During my user testing process, I found that most people skip over intro tours as quickly as possible ant those that didn\'t rarely remember what they were supposed to learn, because they haven\'t seen the interface yet so they don\'t have any sense of where and how the tips they\'re learning will apply. Here comes the <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Just_in_Time_Teaching\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Just In Time Education<\\/a><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Just_in_Time_Teaching\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\"><\\/a><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/en.wikipedia.org\\/wiki\\/Just_in_Time_Teaching\\\"><\\/a> concept.<br><\\/p><p>I\'ve tried different methods to solve this problem. For example, by overlaying the tuts on top of the actual interface design, but even so, people lack the experience to know ehich actions will be useful to them and when. Besides, over time they\'ve likely to forget some of the functions since they didn\'t take that action immediately after they\'ve learnt. <\\/p><p>So instead of trying to teach everything up front and all at once, teach in the moment when specific information is actually useful. In my case, I tried to provide only the nessasary tips for visitors, for instance, if a user start exploring the 3D scence by click, I will suggest him scroll mouse wheel, vice versa. Besides, . Last but not least, the \\\"how to\\\" instruction is always on the left corner of the page, make it easier for visitors to check out anytime.<\\/p><p>The trick to getting just in time education right is revealing useful information when people actually need it not when they don\'t.<\\/p>\",\"21\":\"What I\'ve Learned\",\"43\":[\"92\"],\"17\":\"\",\"18\":\"\",\"16\":\"\",\"13\":[\"7\"],\"42\":[\"110\"],\"50\":\"http:\\/\\/realtimefengshui.com\\/\",\"44\":[\"80\"],\"12\":\"UX, Interface Design, Modeling & Visual Design, User Research &Testing, Content Strategy\",\"3\":\"The project is designed to present abstract feng shui principles, its philosophy, as well as its applications in modern interior design through creative 3D interactive experience.\",\"9\":[\"aftereffects\",\"flash\",\"photoshop\",\"blender\",\"html5\",\"sketch\",\"webgl\"],\"4\":\"2014\"}}', '2015-10-17 22:01:20', '2015-10-17 22:01:20', '3b9f45cd-ff04-487c-b2c4-29992abe5a2b'),
