 ('26', 'field', '20', 'en_us', ' kanjy is a community platform dedicated to emerging and established screenwriters playwrights agents producers organizations and venues the original website could be found at https kanjy co kanjy s objective is to provide a single platform that can connect and organize vast artist communities specifically related to writers however there are several problems on the site that might drag kanjy away from even more traffic the page doesn t impress me as a first time visitor after seeing a few slides in the header image area it simply was not able to convey what it is the look and feel of the overall layout didn t match its content the logo could also be redesigned to be more coherent to a writer s community there is no quick upload functionality for sharing your work and the sign up process is too long kanjy allows writers to create portfolios of their work but it s still not sufficient to make the whole community an active network the connection between writers and publishers needs to be tightened as an even closer relationship i tried to solve these issues by adapting a near black and white color scheme which is inspired by newspaper and hand writing imageries adding a quick upload button for registered users to submit their work as soon as they want encouraging a new user to join by showing the numbers of the current user base writer agents producers organizations and venues and created a author of the week section in the home page finally the site was made responsive for users to read and share from almost any given platform '),
